Overview

This was built for the course: Developing Data Products as part of the Coursera Data Science Specialization.

The shiny app developed for this assignment is avalilable: https://erginozcan.shinyapps.io/AssociationExams/

The source codes of ui.R and server.R and are available on the GitHub repo: https://erginozcan.shinyapps.io/AssociationExams/
Exam Marks Calculation and Interpretation

The average mark for the three exams written is calculated based on the following formula:

Average mark = (w + x + y + z) / 4

Where:

    w =  Society Information Score
    x =  Database Score
    y =  Foreign Language Score
    z =  Accounting Score

Exam Intrepretation

Example: For a score of 65 at Society Information, 

Average Score is 

    Average <50, : Failed
    Average [50-59] , : Considered for the junior association participate position
    Average [60-69] , : Considered for the association participate position
    Average [70-79] , : Considered for the association specialist position
    Average [80-89] , :Considered for the association manager trainee position
    Average >= 90 : Considered for the association manager position

